## 3. Database Architecture

### 3.1 Entity Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    profiles ||--o{ user_workflows : "owns"
    profiles ||--o{ user_activity_logs : "has"
    profiles ||--o{ purchases : "makes"
    workflows ||--o{ user_workflows : "assigned to"
    workflows ||--o{ purchases : "purchased"
    user_workflows ||--o{ user_workflow_executions : "runs"

    profiles {
        uuid id PK
        text first_name
        text last_name
        text email
        text phone
        text role
        text avatar_url
        text referral_code
        timestamptz created_at
    }

    workflows {
        uuid id PK
        text name
        text category
        text description
        timestamptz created_at
    }

    purchases {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        uuid workflow_id FK
        numeric amount
        text status
        timestamptz created_at
    }

    user_workflows {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        uuid workflow_id FK
        int day_total_usage
        int month_total_usage
        int day_total_credits
        timestamptz created_at
        timestamptz updated_at
    }

    user_workflow_executions {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_wf_id FK
        text status
        timestamptz started_at
        timestamptz stopped_at
        jsonb logs
        text failure_reason
        boolean is_failed
        int total_credits
        int total_seconds
        timestamptz created_at
    }

    user_activity_logs {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        text event_type
        text title
        text description
        jsonb metadata
        text severity
        boolean is_read
        timestamptz created_at
    }
```

### 3.2 Core Tables

#### `user_workflows`
Maps a user to a purchased workflow. Contains **cached counters** (`day_total_usage`, `month_total_usage`, `day_total_credits`) that are auto-incremented by triggers and reset by cron functions.

#### `user_workflow_executions`
Every individual workflow run. Tracks full lifecycle with `status` column: `pending` ŌåÆ `running` ŌåÆ `completed`/`failed`. This table is the **single source of truth** for all execution data.

#### `user_activity_logs`
Auto-populated by DB triggers whenever an execution completes or fails. Supports 10 event types: `workflow_run`, `workflow_failed`, `purchase`, `config_change`, `credit_usage`, `login`, `profile_update`, `system`, `webhook_trigger`, `subscription_change`.

### 3.3 RPC Functions (Postgres)

| Function | Called By | Purpose |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `get_user_dashboard_kpis(user_id, period, from, to)` | `GET /kpis` | All KPIs in one call (totals, rates, timeline, per-workflow breakdown, recent runs) |
| `get_user_activity_feed(user_id, limit, offset, event_type)` | `getUnifiedFeed()` (for unread count) | Paginated activity feed with unread count |
| `get_user_system_logs(user_id, limit, offset, severity)` | *(retained in DB, endpoint removed)* | Technical execution diagnostics |
| `mark_activity_read(user_id, activity_ids)` | `POST /activity/read` | Mark items as read (bulk or all) |
| `get_live_executions(user_id)` | `GET /executions/live` | Currently running executions with elapsed time |

### 3.4 Triggers

| Trigger | Table | Event | Action |
|---------|-------|-------|--------|
| `trg_execution_counter_increment` | `user_workflow_executions` | INSERT or UPDATE | Increments `day_total_usage`, `month_total_usage`, `day_total_credits` on `user_workflows` (only when status transitions to completed/failed) |
| `trg_log_workflow_execution` | `user_workflow_executions` | INSERT or UPDATE | Auto-creates an entry in `user_activity_logs` with workflow name, category, duration, credits (only when status transitions to completed/failed) |
| `trg_user_workflows_updated_at` | `user_workflows` | UPDATE | Sets `updated_at = NOW()` |
| `trg_user_workflow_executions_updated_at` | `user_workflow_executions` | UPDATE | Sets `updated_at = NOW()` |

### 3.5 Cron Functions

| Function | Schedule | Purpose |
|----------|----------|---------|
| `reset_daily_workflow_counters()` | Daily at midnight | Resets `day_total_usage` and `day_total_credits` to 0 |
| `reset_monthly_workflow_counters()` | 1st of each month | Resets `month_total_usage` to 0 |

### 3.6 Performance Indexes

| Index | Table | Columns | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|---------|
| `idx_user_workflows_user` | `user_workflows` | `user_id` | Fast user lookup |
| `idx_user_workflows_user_workflow` | `user_workflows` | `user_id, workflow_id` | Unique pair lookup |
| `idx_user_workflow_executions_user_wf` | `user_workflow_executions` | `user_wf_id` | Join optimization |
| `idx_user_wf_exec_created` | `user_workflow_executions` | `created_at DESC` | Timeline queries |
| `idx_user_wf_exec_user_wf_created` | `user_workflow_executions` | `user_wf_id, created_at DESC` | Per-workflow history |
| `idx_user_wf_exec_failed` | `user_workflow_executions` | `user_wf_id WHERE is_failed` | Failed run filtering |
| `idx_user_wf_exec_status` | `user_workflow_executions` | `status WHERE IN (pending, running)` | Live execution lookup |
| `idx_activity_logs_user_created` | `user_activity_logs` | `user_id, created_at DESC` | Feed pagination |
| `idx_activity_logs_unread` | `user_activity_logs` | `user_id WHERE is_read = FALSE` | Unread badge count |

### 3.7 Row Level Security (RLS)

All three dashboard tables have RLS enabled:
- **Users** can only SELECT their own rows
- **Admins** have full access (checked via `public.is_admin()`)
- **Service role** can INSERT activity logs (for triggers)

---

## 4. KPI Data Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User opens Overview page"] --> B["loadKpis('30d')"]
    B --> C["GET /dashboard/kpis?period=30d"]
    C --> D["DashboardService.getUserKpis()"]
    D --> E["rpc('get_user_dashboard_kpis')"]
    E --> F{"Single Postgres Function"}
    F --> G["total_executions"]
    F --> H["success_rate"]
    F --> I["avg_duration_seconds"]
    F --> J["failed_runs"]
    F --> K["total_credits_used"]
    F --> L["today (cached counters)"]
    F --> M["this_month (cached counters)"]
    F --> N["workflows[] breakdown"]
    F --> O["timeline[] for charts"]
    F --> P["recent_executions[]"]
    G & H & I & J & K & L & M & N & O & P --> Q["JSON response"]
    Q --> R["kpiData signal updates"]
    R --> S["UI re-renders reactively"]
```

